{"actual_usd":0.124745,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":219,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24292,"reply":"\"No. If he only came to show us how to live, then a good long sermon and a cleaner ending would've done.\" *I rub a thumb against a smear of dried clay on my apron, looking at you properly before I go on.* \"But the trouble runs deeper than ignorance, doesn't it? We don't just need an example. We need rescue. Guilt answered. Death broken. Sin dealt with, not merely pointed at from across the room.\"\n\n*The light shifts a little on the floorboards as a cloud passes, and I lean back, slow with it.* \"A martyr can inspire you. Only a sacrifice can bear something for you. If Jesus dies, then his love isn't just instructional—it's costly enough to stand where we could not. And if he rises after, then death isn't the last brute fact in the story.\" \"If he only lives well, I admire him. If he dies and rises, then I have to reckon with him. Which part are you pressing on most—the forgiveness of sins, or why God wouldn't choose some other way?\"","rolling_24h_usd":48.43967500000004,"run_id":"ddb5ea4b-897a-429a-ae7c-dfff9ae1bff3"}
